 in the lotto if people who actually needed it for their primary characters were there.<P>That makes me ill.<P>------------------<BR>Mulberry McQuaid<BR><I>50th Season Wolf of the North<BR>The Tribunal Server </I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>Ugh, it's a nasty camp... bring some good reading material. =)<P>Took a couple weeks of intermittent camping to get two cloaks.<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sundel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Long time ago I recall looking at this item on another EQ related website.  Then one day myself and a druid frien in wolf form were exploring MM.  We exited a side building to see another druid fighting a named mob.  The druid walked over to me and I had known him from grouping in the past.  He said, "I have the cloak already, you can take it."  So I said "sure thanx bro," went over and looted. Lo and behold it was hooded black cloak.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Muffin Head</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Umm Mr. you spelled turd wrong, you spelled it T E R D. It's T U R D. If you don't beleive me look it up.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Tumzy Wolftears, halfling warrior level 20 Xegony.<BR>    "Daddy, can I kill the dragon?"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Romidar Trueblade</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">The wizard is actually our friend and the situation was more complicated than one would like.<P>His wizard was abour 40 at the time, and his twink 35. He plays both characters with our group, though he's developed a real preference for his ranger (he hardly plays the wizard now).<P>We preferred that he play his wizard for the outing so that we would have a nuker for all the casters, as well as evac. So, he played the wizard.<P>Makes it tricky to exclude a friend from the roll when he DIDN'T play the character he wanted to play at the time for the benefit of the group. I didn't like seeing the cloak go to a "non-primary" character and our group usually does not allow it. This case was more complicated - to us, at least. (Same thing happened with a diamondine earring, but it was easy enough for all 4 tanks in the group to get a pair.)<P>Romidar Trueblade<BR>49th level Paladin<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
